This paper focuses on the problem of online ranker evaluation in information retrieval, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving the K-armed dueling bandit problem, which is a machine learning problem that falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also utilizes a divide-and-conquer strategy, which is a common technique in the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm's performance using examples from the domain of online evaluation for web search, which falls under the category of Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
